title: Business Council of Australia - Wikipedia
snippet: The Business Council of Australia (BCA) is an industry association that comprises the chief executives of more than 130 of Australia's biggest corporations. It was formed in 1983 by the merger of the Business Roundtable – a spin-off of the Committee for Economic Development of Australia – and the Australian Industry Development Association.

title: Business Council of Australia
snippet: The Business Council of Australia brings together the experience and capability of chief executives and their teams from across a diverse range of industries to develop common-sense, trusted and evidence-based policies.

title: Who We Are - Business Council of Australia - V1
snippet: The Business Council of Australia provides a forum for Australian business leaders to contribute directly to public policy debates. We have helped to initiate and shape the key economic and business reform debates that have underpinned Australia’s economic resurgence. This section contains information about our structure, policy agenda and policymaking process, and about our membership, board, policymaking committees and task forces, and our staff.
